description: Defines the MPDS API input queries (q-parameter) and output data (S = crystal structures, P = physical properties, and C = phase diagrams)

props.description: Any of the three levels of the physical properties (domains, categories and properties per se, see https://mpds.io/#hierarchy); SINGLE: combination of several terms is not allowed

elements.description: Chemical elements; equal or greater element count in a compound is returned; MULTIPLE: combination of several terms is allowed (separate by minus)

classes.description: Various groups of terms: i.e. mineral names, periodic groups, physical classes, element count keywords etc., nearly 4500 in total; MULTIPLE: combination of several terms is allowed (separate by comma)

lattices.description: Crystal system; SINGLE: combination of several terms is not allowed

formulae.description: Chemical formula; SINGLE: combination of several terms is not allowed

sgs.description: Space group; SINGLE: combination of several terms is not allowed

protos.description: Prototype system (Strukturbericht symbol like D01 or formula *vs.* Pearson symbol *vs.* space group number like CaTiO3 cP5 221), nearly 14000 unique distinct prototypes, including about 250 Strukturbericht symbols; SINGLE: combination of several terms is not allowed

aeatoms.description: Polyhedron atoms (center and ligands) e.g. Ag, X-Se, TiO6, TiX6 (X stands for any element); SINGLE: combination of several terms is not allowed

aetype.description: Polyhedral type (with CN); SINGLE: combination of several terms is not allowed
enum: square pyramid central atom outside or base plane 5-vertex

authors.description: Original publication author(s); MULTIPLE: combination of several terms is allowed (separate by comma)

codens.description: International 6-symbol CODEN of a journal; SINGLE: combination of several terms is not allowed

years.description: Original publication years; MULTIPLE: combination of several terms is allowed (e.g. 1990-2018, maximum timespan is 50 years)

geos.description: *Country* or *city* (*areas* such as lands, cantons, etc. are currently not fully supported); SINGLE: combination of several terms is not allowed

orgs.description: Organization, hosting the research (this field is currently not fully standardized); SINGLE: combination of several terms is not allowed

phase.description: Unique material phase (according to the LPF distinct phases concept), can be none

phase_id.description: Unique material phase identifier (according to the LPF distinct phases concept), can be none

prototype.description: Prototype system: chemical formula, Pearson symbol, and space group number

sg_hm.description: International or Hermann-Mauguin notation of the space group

cell_abc.description: Standardized crystal cell as _a_, _b_, _c_, _alpha_, _beta_, _gamma_, in angstroms and degrees

symops.description: Symmetry operations for CIF, according to [IUCR](http://www.iucr.org/__data/iucr/cifdic_html/1/cif_core.dic/Ispace_group_symop_operation_xyz.html)

labels_noneq.description: Non-equivalent atomic labels, may contain important information, such as hydroxyl label

occs_noneq.description: Non-equivalent atomic site occupancies, according to [IUCR](http://www.iucr.org/__data/iucr/cifdic_html/1/cif_core.dic/Iatom_site_occupancy.html)

periodic_nums_noneq.description: Periodic numbers (not to confuse with the atomic numbers) for chemical elements in the crystalline structure

phase.description: Persistent URL of the distinct phase

v.description: Standardized cell volume, in cubic angstroms

r_factors.description: R factors (if available); in high quality determinations must be less than 0.03

condition.description: Temperature (K) and pressure (GPa) for cell and structure determination (if non-standard)

comments.description: Editors' comments concerning the data extraction and processing

sample.description: Citrine's MIF root container, according to https://github.com/CitrineInformatics/mif-documentation

chemical_formula.description: Chemical formula (denoted as chemicalFormula in Citrine's MIF); may contain impurity element(s), denoted by fractional content or *x*; can be extended with the phase label, e.g. *rt*

condition.description: MIF's information about the inherent conditions of the system as a whole (currently contains only a space group number)

phase.description: Unique material phase (according to the LPF distinct phases concept), can be none

phase_id.description: Unique material phase identifier (according to the LPF distinct phases concept), can be none

data_type.description: MIF's dataType, controlled either by the *dtype* request parameter or by a suitable *classes* keyword

property.description: MIF's name, value, and units of the measured property, augmented with the LPF domain-category hierarchy

scalar.description: Note that the value is represented by string if out of 2^32 bounds

condition.description: MIF's details of the external conditions (if available) applied during a measurement

phase.description: Persistent URL of the distinct phase

arity.description: Elements count for the whole phase diagram

diatype.description: Phase diagram type (mostly actual for the *arity* > 2, i.e. ternaries, quaternaries etc.)

chemical_elements.description: Valid chemical elements of the phase diagram

title_a.description: Triangular plot only: the first component (left triangle corner)

range_a.description: Triangular plot only: the first component range

title_b.description: Triangular plot only: the second component (upper triangle corner)

range_b.description: Triangular plot only: the second component range

title_c.description: Triangular plot only: the third component (right triangle corner)

range_c.description: Triangular plot only: the third component range

comp_a.description: Triangular plot only: left triangle corner composition as element_A -> content_A, element_B -> content_B etc.

comp_b.description: Triangular plot only: upper triangle corner composition as element_A -> content_A, element_B -> content_B etc.

comp_c.description: Triangular plot only: right triangle corner composition as element_A -> content_A, element_B -> content_B etc.

comp_start.description: Rectangular plot only: left edge composition as element_A -> content_A, element_B -> content_B etc.

comp_end.description: Rectangular plot only: right edge composition as element_A -> content_A, element_B -> content_B etc.

temp.description: Rectangular plot: temperature range (Y-axis); triangular plot: isotherm value(s) or none for *projection* *diatypes*; always in Celsius;

labels.description: Labels, as extracted from the phase diagram vector image; can be referred by *reflabel* attribute of *shapes*; contain title and coordinates

shapes.description: Phase areas data, as extracted from the phase diagram vector image

kind.description: Shape kind: *phase* and *compound* is semantically meaningful (has several attributes), whereas *drawing* is used for visualization only (has only *svgpath* attribute)

svgpath.description: Phase areas represented in SVG standard notation, see http://www.w3.org/TR/SVG/paths.html

label.description: Label, as extracted from the phase diagram vector image; can be none

reflabel.description: A reference to *labels* item, which should be used for visualization only; can be none

phase_id.description: Unique material phase identifier (according to the LPF distinct phases concept); only relevant for *nphases* = 1; can be none;

is_solid.description: Label for a state of aggregation, showing an absense of liquid or gas phases; can be absent

chemical_elements.description: Valid chemical elements of the *phase* or *compound*; only relevant for *nphases* = 1; can be absent
